oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Bob Wills Live at the Knights of Columbus Hall - 1955-11-24 - Reel 2
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The recording is of Bob Wills (musician) live at the Knights of Columbus Hall in Bryan, Texas. The performance is accompanied by the Texas Playboys: Eldon Shamblin, Lou Walker, Billy Bowman (steel guitar), Art McNulty (piano), Johnny Dalton (drums), Lee Ross (vocal and bass), and Marvin Shaw (trumpet). The recording is from November 24, 1955. The tape is labeled reel two.
